CM_ BU_ DMU_VEDS "Voith ECU";
CM_ BU_ VIC "VIC";
CM_ BU_ Vehicle_Control_Unit "Vector__XXX";
CM_ BO_ 2364606963 "Collection of data the High Voltage Energy Storage System (or Pack 1 in systems with only one pack) Thermal Management System sends to the Hybrid Controller.
";
CM_ SG_ 2364606963 ThermMngtSysCooltLvl "Indicates the coolant level in the High Voltage Energy Storage System (or Pack 1 in systems with only one pack) Thermal Management System.
00b = Coolant Level is not sufficient
01b = Coolant Level is sufficient
10b = Error
11b = Not Available";
CM_ SG_ 2364606963 ThermMngtSysMode "Indicates the operating mode of the Thermal Management System.The heat transfer medium may be (e.g. liquid or air).  The cooling system may be fans, liquid coolant, or a combination of mediums.";
CM_ SG_ 2364606963 ThermMngtSysHVILSts "Status of the High Voltage Interlock Loop from the viewpoint of the High Voltage Energy Storage System Thermal Management System 1.
00b = HVIL Closed
01b = HVIL Open
10b = Error
11b = Not Available";
CM_ SG_ 2364606963 ThermMngtSysHeatrSts "The state of the High Voltage Energy Storage System (or Pack 1 in systems with only one pack) heater.
00b = Heater Off
01b = Heater On
10b = Error 
11b = Not Available";
CM_ SG_ 2364606963 ThermMngtSysRel "When the High Voltage Energy Storage System (or Pack 1 in systems with only one pack) Thermal Management System is equipped with a relative humidity sensor, this is the  measured Relative Humidity";
CM_ SG_ 2364606963 ThermMngtSysCmpr "When the High Voltage Energy Storage System (or Pack 1 in systems with only one pack) Thermal Management System is equipped with an active cooling system (e.g. air conditioner), this is the Compressor Speed.";
CM_ SG_ 2364606963 ThermMngtSysHv "This is the high-voltage power consumed by this Thermal Management System (TMS). If there is only one pack, or a single TMS for the entire HVES system, then this represents the total high-voltage power consumed.";
CM_ SG_ 2364606963 ThermMngtSysSLIInpPwr "This is the low-voltage power consumed by this Thermal Management System (TMS). If there is only one pack, or a single TMS for the entire HVES system, then this represents the total low-voltage power consumed.";
CM_ BO_ 2632712179 "- J1939/21 Transport Protocol packets, functional content is defined in the message using the protocol";
