CM_ BO_ 2566844672 "Cruise Control/Vehicle Speed 1
";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Engine_Shutdwn_Ovride_Swtch "Switch signal which indicates the position of the engine shutdown override switch. 

00b = Off
01b = On
10b = Error
11b = Not available



";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Engine_Diag_Test_Mode_Swtch "Switch signal which indicates the position of the engine diagnostic test mode switch.

00b = Off
01b = On
10b = Error
11b = Not available



";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Engine_Idle_Decrement_Switch "Switch signal which indicates the position of the idle decrement switch.

00b = Off
01b = On
10b = Error
11b = Not available


";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Engine_Idle_Increment_Switch "Switch signal which indicates the position of the idle increment switch.

00b = Off
01b = On
10b = Error
11b = Not available


";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Cruise_Control_States "This parameter is used to indicate the current state, or mode, of operation by the cruise control device.
000b = Off/Disabled
001b = Hold
010b = Accelerate
011b = Decelerate
100b = Resume
101b = Set
110b = Accel Override
111b = Not available


";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 PTO_Governor_State "This parameter is used to indicate the current state or mode of operation by the power takeoff (PTO) governor.
00000b = Off/Disabled
00001b = Hold
00010b = Remote Hold
00011b = Standby
00100b = Remote Standby
00101b = Set



";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Cruise_Control_Set_Spd "Value of set (chosen) velocity of velocity control system. 
If an algorithm that can modify the cruise control set point exists in the system.



";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Cruise_Control_Accelerate_Swtch "Switch signal of the cruise control activator which indicates that the activator is in the position accelerate.

00b = Cruise control act not in the pos accel
01b = Cruise control activator in position accelerate
10b = Error
11b = Not available

";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Cruise_Control_Resume_Swtch "Switch signal of the cruise control activator which indicates that the activator is in the position resume.

00b = Cruise control act not in the pos resume
01b = Cruise control activator in position resume
10b = Error
11b = Not available
";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Cruise_Control_Coast_Decl_Switch "Switch signal of the cruise control activator which indicates that the activator is in the position coast (decelerate).

00b = Cruise control act not in the pos coast
01b = Cruise control activator in position coast
10b = Error
11b = Not available
";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Cruise_Control_SetSwtch "Switch signal of the cruise control activator which indicates that the activator is in the position set.

00b = Cruise control activator not in the position set
01b = Cruise control activator in position set
10b = Error
11b = Not available

";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Clutch_Switch "Switch signal which indicates that the clutch pedal is being pressed.

00b = Clutch pedal released
01b = Clutch pedal depressed
10b = Error
11b = Not available
";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Brake_Switch "Switch signal which indicates that the driver operated brake foot pedal is being pressed.

00b = Brake pedal released
01b = Brake pedal depressed
10b = Error
11b = Not Available
";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Cruise_Control_Enable_Swtch "Switch signal which indicates that it is possible to manage the cruise control function.

00b = Cruise control disabled
01b = Cruise control enabled
10b = Error
11b = Not available

";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Cruise_Control_Active "Cruise control is switched on.  It is not ensured that the engine is controlled by cruise control. 

00b = Cruise control switched off
01b = Cruise control switched on
10b = Error
11b = Not available

";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Wheel_Based_Veh_Spd "Speed of the vehicle as calculated from wheel or tailshaft speed.
";
CM_ SG_ 2566844672 Cruise_Control_Pause_Swtch "Switch signal which indicates the position of the Cruise Control Pause Switch used on Remote Cruise Control applications.

