VAL_ 2498795251 HS_StofChSts 15 "1111b = Not  Available" 14 "1110b = Error" 13 "1101b = Reserved" 12 "1100b = Reserved" 11 "1011b = Reserved" 10 "1010b = Reserved" 9 "1001b = Reserved" 8 "1000b = Reserved" 7 "0111b = Reserved" 6 "0110b = SOC is above its recommended upper limit" 5 "0101b = SOC is at its recommended upper limit" 4 "0100b = SOC is approaching its recommended upper limit" 3 "0011b = SOC is below its recommended lower limit" 2 "0010b = SOC is at its recommended lower limit" 1 "0001b = SOC is approaching its recommended lower limit" 0 "0000b = SOC level is acceptable." ;
VAL_ 2498795251 HS_CellBalSts 3 "11b = Not Available" 2 "10b = Error" 1 "01b = Cells are unbalanced" 0 "00b = Cells are balanced" ;
VAL_ 2498795251 HS_CellBalnAcv 3 "11b = Not Available" 2 "10b = Error" 1 "01b = Cell balancing is active" 0 "00b = Cell balancing is not active" ;
VAL_ 2498795251 HS_IntChrgrSts 3 "11b = Not Available" 2 "10b = Error" 1 "01b = Charging on" 0 "00b = Charging off" ;
VAL_ 2498795251 HS_HiUBusCnctnSts 15 "1111b = Not Available" 14 "1110b = Error" 13 "1101b = Reserved" 12 "1100b = Reserved" 11 "1011b = Reserved" 10 "1010b = Reserved" 9 "1001b = Reserved" 8 "1000b = Reserved" 7 "0111b = Reserved" 6 "0110b = Reserved" 5 "0101b = Reserved" 4 "0100b = Disconnected; Precharge Failed.  Indicates that the pre-charge function status cannot be determined or did not complete (e.g. Relay failure, insufficient HVES voltage, etc.)." 3 "0011b = Disconnection in Process.   May be rapidly transitioned through depending on HVES design, but indicates that HVES1 is in the process of disconnecting itself from the high voltage bus." 2 "0010b = Connection in Process.  May be rapidly transitioned through depending on HVES design, but indicates that the precharge relay is closed and/or one or more contactors may also be closed or in the process of being closed." 1 "0001b = Connected.  All contactors are closed and the precharge relay is open.  Typically results from the SPN 8123 (HVESS High-Voltage Bus Connect Command) ." 0 "0000b = Disconnected.  One or more contactors are open.  State may result from the SPN 8123 (HVESS High-Voltage Bus Connect Command) or due to a limit being exceeded." ;
VAL_ 2498795251 HS_OperationalSts 15 "1111b = Not Available" 14 "1110b = Error" 13 "1101b = Reserved" 12 "1100b = Reserved" 11 "1011b = Reserved" 10 "1010b = Reserved" 9 "1001b = Reserved" 8 "1000b = Reserved" 7 "0111b = Reserved" 6 "0110b = Disabled by internal decision of HVES controller (e.g. malfunction, protection)" 5 "0101b = Disabled by external command.  The HVES is in a non-operational state due to a Power Down Command, or the result of Operation Consent being revoked." 4 "0100b = Emergency Power-Down In Process.  This state is a response to Power Down Command state 10b." 3 "0011b = Normal Power-Down in Process.  This state is a response to Power Down Command state 01b." 2 "0010b = Operational." 1 "0001b = Initialization Complete, awaiting Operation Consent.  HVES controller is ready from its perspective, but requires one or more positive Operation Consent indications before becoming fully operational.  Some applications may not support this state." 0 "0000b = Initialization in process.  The HVES controller is powering up.  This process may include both internal HVES controller checks, as well as system checks being run by the HVES controller." ;

